  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/ 160&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Grind the<strong> fennel seeds</strong>&nbsp;in a pestle and mortar roughly</p>\r\n<p>Score the fatty side of the <strong>pork belly</strong> in a criss-cross pattern by drawing a sharp knife through the skin, deep enough to reach the meat below</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rub the scored fat with<strong> salt</strong>, the<strong> fennel seeds</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong>&ndash;try to rub the seasoning deep into the criss-cross pattern</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once very hot, add the <strong>pork</strong>, skin-side down and cook for 5-8 min or until nicely coloured on the fat side only</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>pork</strong> (wipe the pan clean and keep it for the next step!) fat-side up, to a baking tray</p>\r\n<p>Put it in the oven for 40-50 min, or until it's crispy, coloured, and cooked through</p>\r\n<p>Tip: use tin foil to avoid mess!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>lentils</strong>&nbsp;in a sieve under the cold tap, then add them to the reserved pan&nbsp;with 1 L <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.5 L]</span>&nbsp;cold water</p>\r\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 20-25 min or until the lentils are tender</p>\r\n<p>Once softened, drain the lentils and run them under cold water</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix the&nbsp;<strong>mustard</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar,</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>honey</strong> together with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> - this is your dressing</p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/575.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>pork belly</strong> from the oven, transfer to a chopping board and allow to rest for 5-10 min</p>\r\n<p>Mix&nbsp;the cooked, drained, cooled lentils (keep the pan for the next step!) with the <strong>dressing</strong>, grated <strong>carrot</strong>&nbsp;and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Toss the <strong>pea shoots</strong> and dressed lentils together&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
